"title": "5181: sitting",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5181: sitting",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A bodily posture associated with resting, eating or instruction. When used of God, the image often conveys the idea of kingly authority over creation.</p>\n<h2>Sitting to rest</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:1\">GEN 18:1</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:6\">JHN 4:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:15\">EXO 2:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod17:12\">EXO 17:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:4\">1KI 19:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:36\">MAT 26:36</a></p>\n<h2>Sitting to eat</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:6\">EXO 32:6</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:7\">LUK 17:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:6\">JDG 19:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:14\">RUT 2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam20:24\">1SA 20:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:1\">PRO 23:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer16:8\">JER 16:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:19\">MAT 14:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:7\">1CO 10:7</a></p>\n<h2>Sitting to teach or to learn</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:1-Matt5:2\">MAT 5:1–5:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:2\">MAT 13:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:35\">MRK 9:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:46\">LUK 2:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:39\">LUK 10:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:2\">JHN 8:2</a></p>\n<h2>Sitting for prayer</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg21:2\">JDG 21:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:18\">2SA 7:18</a></p>\n<h2>Sitting as a sign of authority</h2>\n<h3>Human authority</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod11:5\">EXO 11:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:13\">1KI 1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs3:6\">1KI 3:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs10:30\">2KI 10:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech6:13\">ZEC 6:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:37\">MRK 10:37</a></p>\n<h3>Divine authority</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps29:10\">PSA 29:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:19\">1KI 22:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps47:8\">PSA 47:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps80:1\">PSA 80:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:1\">ISA 6:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:64\">MAT 26:64</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:42\">LUK 20:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:3\">HEB 1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:12\">HEB 10:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:2\">HEB 12:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:21\">REV 3:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:10\">REV 4:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:10\">REV 7:10</a></p>\n<h2>Sitting to judge</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod18:13\">EXO 18:13</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:31\">MAT 25:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam19:8\">2SA 19:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:8\">PRO 20:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa28:6\">ISA 28:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer38:7\">JER 38:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:26\">DAN 7:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel3:12\">JOL 3:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:19\">MAT 27:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:30\">LUK 22:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:3\">ACT 23:3</a></p>\n<h2>Sitting as a sign of possession and peace</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic4:4\">MIC 4:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech3:10\">ZEC 3:10</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ seated at God's right hand</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:69\">LUK 22:69</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:20\">EPH 1:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:6\">EPH 2:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:1\">COL 3:1</a></p>",
